```
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# create a sample dataframe
data = {'col1': [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], 'col2': [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# plot the two columns
plt.plot(df['col1'], label='Column 1')
plt.plot(df['col2'], label='Column 2')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
```
This will create a line plot that compares the values in the two columns of the dataframe. The x-axis will be the index of the dataframe, and the y-axis will be the values in the two columns. The plot will also include a legend to show which column is which.
